FBIS4-9310 "dreeu079_i_94008" FBIS-EEU-94-079 Daily Report 24 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Serbian Snipers Kill Two Serbian Snipers Kill Two LD2404142994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 24 Apr 94 LD2404142994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Report by unidentified reporter from Gorazde--recorded] [Excerpts] We are in twelfth hour since the expiration of the NATO ultimatum deadline for the withdrawal of the chetniks outside the three-km exclusion zone around Gorazde. That NATO can easily forget its ultimatum issued to the Serbs is best confirmed by chetnik snipers who killed two women this morning: One was killed in the suburb of [name indistinct], and another one was killed on the bridge over the Drina River in the central part of the town. According to details available to us at the moment, they have also wounded 15 people. [passage omitted] The latest reports from the region of Kopaci say that an armored personnel carrier arrived in the suburb of (?Kokino Selo) bringing in fascists who are systematically setting fire to houses in the suburb and laying antipersonnel mines. Strong explosions are reverberating in the region of Pobjeda enterprise: plants belonging to this industrial complex are being destroyed. When this report was filed we heard from Pobjeda enterprise that chetnik shells completely devastated the only (?auxiliary) water supply system with nonpotable water, though it has been used as drinking water for the past two years. Now the population can use only several freshwater sources in the central part of the town, but they are under constant sniper fire coming from the other bank of the Drina River. [passage omitted]
